  <p>According to Poppenreiter, Ohlala seeks to improve upon two perceived flaws that Tinder and other dating apps often fall into. First, the in-app chats that go nowhere ‚Äî or worse, promising matches who ghost on you. As more results-oriented users of Tinder or OkCupid can attest, if you‚Äôve logged on with the objective to meet up with someone that night, you can often be left frustrated. With Ohlala, everyone wants something, and everyone‚Äôs on a tight schedule.</p>
